content: # PUT vs POST on `/vault/{path}` — Detailed Behavior Analysis

Based on the codebase, here's a comprehensive breakdown of the differences between PUT and POST operations:

## PUT `/vault/{path}` — Create or Replace

**Purpose:** Create a new file or completely replace an existing file's content.

### Behavior:
```typescript
// From src/requestHandler.ts, _vaultPut method
async _vaultPut(filepath: string, req: express.Request, res: express.Response) {
  // Creates parent directories if needed
  await this.app.vault.createFolder(path.dirname(filepath));

  // Text content
  if (isContentType(contentType)) {
    await this.app.vault.adapter.write(filepath, req.body);
  } 
  // Binary content
  else {
    await this.app.vault.adapter.writeBinary(filepath, toArrayBuffer(req.body));
  }
}
```

### Key Characteristics:
- **Idempotent:** ✅ Yes — multiple identical requests produce the same result
- **File exists:** Completely replaces the entire file content
- **File doesn't exist:** Creates a new file with the provided content
- **Content-Type:** Accepts both text (`text/markdown`, `text/plain`) and binary (`image/jpeg`, etc.)
- **Status Code:** `204 No Content` on success

### Example:
```bash
# Replace entire file (or create if new)
curl -k -X PUT \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <api-key>" \
  -H "Content-Type: text/markdown" \
  --data "This completely replaces the file" \
  https://127.0.0.1:27124/vault/myfile.md
```

---

## POST `/vault/{path}` — Append Content

**Purpose:** Append content to an existing file or create a new file with the content.

### Behavior:
```typescript
// From src/requestHandler.ts, _vaultPost method
async _vaultPost(filepath: string, req: express.Request, res: express.Response) {
  // Creates parent directories if needed
  await this.app.vault.createFolder(path.dirname(filepath));

  let fileContents = "";
  const file = this.app.vault.getAbstractFileByPath(filepath);

  if (file instanceof TFile) {
    fileContents = await this.app.vault.read(file);
    // Ensures trailing newline before appending
    if (!fileContents.endsWith("\n")) {
      fileContents += "\n";
    }
  }

  fileContents += req.body;
  await this.app.vault.adapter.write(filepath, fileContents);
}
```

### Key Characteristics:
- **Idempotent:** ❌ No — each request appends, creating duplicate content
- **File exists:** Appends content to the end (adds newline if file doesn't end with one)
- **File doesn't exist:** Creates a new file with the provided content
- **Content-Type:** **Only accepts text** (`text/markdown`, `text/plain`) — returns `400` for binary
- **Status Code:** `204 No Content` on success

### Example:
```bash
# Append to existing file
curl -k -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <api-key>" \
  -H "Content-Type: text/markdown" \
  --data "This gets appended to the file" \
  https://127.0.0.1:27124/vault/myfile.md
```

### Test Evidence:
```typescript
// From src/requestHandler.test.ts
test("existing with trailing newline", async () => {
  const arbitraryExistingBytes = "something\nsomething\n";
  app.vault._read = arbitraryExistingBytes;

  await request(server)
    .post(`/vault/${arbitraryFilePath}`)
    .send(arbitraryBytes)
    .expect(204);

  // Result: "something\nsomething\nbytes"
  expect(app.vault.adapter._write).toEqual([
    arbitraryFilePath,
    arbitraryExistingBytes + arbitraryBytes,
  ]);
});

test("existing without trailing newline", async () => {
  const arbitraryExistingBytes = "something\nsomething";

  // Result: "something\nsomething\nbytes" (newline added)
  expect(app.vault.adapter._write).toEqual([
    arbitraryFilePath,
    arbitraryExistingBytes + "\n" + arbitraryBytes,
  ]);
});
```

---

## Content-Type Requirements

### PUT — Flexible:
```typescript
// Accepts text
if (isContentType(contentType)) {
  await this.app.vault.adapter.write(filepath, req.body);
}
// Also accepts binary
else {
  await this.app.vault.adapter.writeBinary(filepath, toArrayBuffer(req.body));
}
```

**Supported:** `text/markdown`, `text/plain`, `image/jpeg`, `image/png`, etc.

### POST — Text Only:
```typescript
if (typeof req.body != "string") {
  this.returnCannedResponse(res, {
    errorCode: ErrorCode.TextContentEncodingRequired,
  });
  return;
}
```

**Supported:** Only `text/markdown` and `text/plain`  
**Rejected:** Binary content types return `400 Bad Request`

---

## Directory Handling

Both operations reject directory paths:

```typescript
if (!filepath || filepath.endsWith("/")) {
  this.returnCannedResponse(res, {
    errorCode: ErrorCode.RequestMethodValidOnlyForFiles,
  });
  return;
}
```

**Test Evidence:**
```typescript
describe("vaultPut", () => {
  test("directory", async () => {
    await request(server).put("/vault/").expect(405);
  });
});

describe("vaultPost", () => {
  test("directory", async () => {
    await request(server).post("/vault/").expect(405);
  });
});
```

---

## Targeted Operations (Sections/Headings)

Both PUT and POST support targeting specific sections via URL paths or headers:

### PUT with Target — Replace Section:
```typescript
// From src/requestHandler.ts, vaultPut method
const resolved = await this._resolvePathAndTarget(rawPath);
if (resolved?.targetType) {
  return this._vaultPatchTargeted(
    resolved.filePath,
    resolved.targetType,
    resolved.target ?? "",
    "replace",  // ← Replace operation
    req,
    res,
  );
}
```

```bash
# Replace content under a heading
curl -k -X PUT \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <api-key>" \
  -H "Content-Type: text/markdown" \
  --data "Replaced content" \
  https://127.0.0.1:27124/vault/myfile.md/heading/My%20Section
```

### POST with Target — Append to Section:
```typescript
// From src/requestHandler.ts, vaultPost method
if (resolved?.targetType) {
  return this._vaultPatchTargeted(
    resolved.filePath,
    resolved.targetType,
    resolved.target ?? "",
    "append",  // ← Append operation
    req,
    res,
  );
}
```

```bash
# Append to a specific heading
curl -k -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <api-key>" \
  -H "Content-Type: text/markdown" \
  --data "Appended content" \
  https://127.0.0.1:27124/vault/myfile.md/heading/My%20Section
```

### Conflict Detection:
```typescript
// Cannot specify target both in URL and headers
if (req.get("Target-Type") || req.get("Target")) {
  this.returnCannedResponse(res, {
    errorCode: ErrorCode.ConflictingTargetSpecification, // Returns 422
  });
  return;
}
```

---

## Quick Reference Table

| Feature | PUT | POST |
|---------|-----|------|
| **Idempotent** | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| **File exists** | Replace entire content | Append to end |
| **File missing** | Create new file | Create new file |
| **Content-Type** | Text + Binary | Text only |
| **Directory path** | ❌ 405 error | ❌ 405 error |
| **Targeted (URL)** | Replace section | Append to section |
| **Targeted (headers)** | Replace section | Append to section |
| **Success code** | 204 | 204 |
| **Newline handling** | None | Adds if missing |

---

## Summary

- **Use PUT** when you want to create or completely replace a file/section (idempotent, supports binary)
- **Use POST** when you want to append content to a file/section (non-idempotent, text only)
- Both create parent directories automatically
- Both support section targeting via URL paths (`/heading/Title`) or headers (`Target-Type`, `Target`)
- POST automatically ensures proper newline separation when appending
